              <additions>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="p1addition1">
                    <locus from="16b" to="16b"/>
                    <p>On the lower half of fol. 16 b the original text has been erased, and a later hand has written the pretended colophon: </p>
                    <p>
                      <quote xml:lang="syr">ܫܠܡ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܕܡܪܝ ܝܘܚܢܢ ܐܝܚܝܕܝܐ ܕܒܗ ܡܠܠ ܘܦܫܩ ܥܠ ܟܠܗܘܢ ܕܘܒܪ̈ܐ ܕܐܝܚ̈ܝܕܝܐ..</quote>
                    </p>
                    <p>Below, on the right side, stand, in the same handwriting, the words: </p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܫܘܒܚܐ ܠܐܒܐ ܕܚܝܠ ܘܠܒܪܐ ܕܣܝܥ ܘܠܪܘܚܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ . . . </quote></p>
                    <p>on the left, </p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܡܢܘ ܕܦܚܡ ܠܡܪܝܐ ܒܫܡܝ ܫܡܝܐ ܘܕܕܡܐ ܠܡܪܝܐ ܒܒ̈ܢܝ ܡ̈ܠܐܟܐ. 
                      ܐܠܗܐ ܩܡ ܒܥܕܬܐ ܕܩܕܝ̈ܫܐ</quote></p>
                    <p>and at the foot of the page, </p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܟܠܗܘܢ ܝܘ̈ܡܝ ܒܚ̈ܛܗܐ ܓܡܪܬ ܐܢܘܢ ܘܒܟܪܡܟ ܡܪܝ ܠܐ ܦܠܚܬ ܐܦܠܐ ܫܥܬܐ ܚܕܐ ܒܪ̈ܚܡܐ ܕܚܢܘ . . . ܣܐ ܥܠ ܪܝܫ ܩܝܣܐ . . . . </quote></p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="p1addition2">
                    <locus from="16b" to="16b"/>
                    <p>The central portion has been carefully effaced  at a still later date, and in its place we now find the following lines, informing us that the manuscript was presented to the  <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/360">convent of S. Mary Deipara</placeName> by its owner <persName ref="">Bar-had-be-shabba</persName></p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr"><sic>ܕܒܪܚܕܒܫܒܐ ܐܟܣܢܝܐ ܕܫܟܢܗ ܠܕܝܪܐ ܕܣܘܪ̈ܪܝܐ
                      ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܘܠܐ ܫܠܝܛ ܠܗ ܡܢ ܐܠܗܐ ܠܐܢܫ ܕܢܫܢܝܗ ܡܢܗ̇ ܏ܘܫ.</sic></quote></p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="3" xml:id="p1addition3">
                    <locus from="1a" to="1a"/>
                    <p>On fol. 1a there are written in an old Arabic hand the words</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="ar">%</quote>, i.e. <quote xml:lang="ar">%</quote>, </p>
                    <p><quote>(the works) of <persName ref="">Amba (Abba) Yuhanna the solitary</persName></quote>.</p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
